#: ../../../reference/hyperlinks.md:1
msgid "Hyperlinks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/hyperlinks.md:3
msgid ""
"Hyperlinks are extremely useful for connecting related topics without having "
"to depart from a clear linear exposition. Sphinx supports various formats "
"for creating hyperlinks, with {any}`sphinx.ext.intersphinx` being a great "
"tool for cross-documentation hyperlinks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/hyperlinks.md:8
msgid ""
"Hyperlinks can take various forms, so here's a list of them:\n"
"\n"
"- standalone hyperlink: https://python.org/\n"
"- hyperlink using references: `link <link>`__\n"
"- hyperlink with inline URL: `link <https://python.org/>`_\n"
"- hyperlink to a different page: :doc:`link <../quickstart>`\n"
"- hyperlink to a specific API element: :class:`pathlib.Path`\n"
"\n"
".. _link: https://python.org/"
msgstr ""

